title: Another quake hits alaska
author: Ap
text: FAIRBANKS - A mild earthquake shook residents of the Prince William Sound community of Valdez early today. It was the third quake to hit Alaska this week.     The temblor struck at 4:34 a.m. A preliminary estimate put its magnitude at 3.9 on the Richter scale. Its epicenter was about 17 miles southwest of Valdez, said Charlotte Rowe, a seismologist with the Alaska Earthquake Information Center.     Although residents reported feeling the quake, there were no reports of damage or injuries.     The same was the case in the two earlier quakes this week: one Sunday that shook the southeastern part of the state and one yesterday that hit the Aleutians.     Sunday's quake, which hit at 8:59 p.m., measured 5.7 on the Richter scale and was centered 90 miles southwest of Haines and 110 miles west of Juneau.     Yesterday's temblor registered 5.3.It hit at 11:54 a.m. and was centered about 90 miles southwest of the island of Adak, about 1,200 miles southwest of Anchorage.     The 1964 Great Alaska Earthquake that killed 131 people measured 8.4 on the Richter scale, while the San Francisco earthquake of 1906 was estimated to register 8.3.
